title: Relativity Space set for maiden launch of Terran 1 rocket
summary: Relativity Space is preparing to conduct the first launch of its Terran 1 rocket Wednesday, in an attempt to become the first 3D-printed and methane-fueled rocket to reach orbit. The Good Luck, Have Fun (GLHF) mission is scheduled for liftoff from Launch Complex 16 (LC-16) at the Cape Canaveral Space Force Station during a three-hour launch window opening at 1 PM EST (18:00 UTC).

title: Shield Capital adds retired general Goldfein to national security advisory board
summary: Shield Capital, a venture firm that invests in defense and space startups, announced that retired U.S. Air Force general David Goldfein has joined its national security advisory board.

title: ISS dodges commercial imaging satellite
summary: The International Space Station adjusted its orbit March 6 to avoid a close approach by an imaging satellite operated by Satellogic, the latest evidence of growing congestion in low Earth orbit.
